column9: *HAD NOSE PRESSED TO BOTTOM OF ARENA AND ROTATED APPEARING AS IF HE WAS INTENSLY SMELLING SOMETHING THERE - BEHAVIOR ENDED WHEN HEAD WAS PICKED UP AGAIN

*TURNED HEAD COMPLETELY SIDEWAYS (90 DEGREES), EXTENDED NECK, OPENED MOUTH, AND BIT AT THE WALL OF THE ARENA - BEHAVIOR BEGAN WITH HEAD TILT AND ENDED WHEN HEAD WAS TILTED BACK UP AGAIN, ONLY ONE EVENT OF THE MOUTH OPENING AND CLOSING WAS OBSERVED
*TURTLE SNAPPED AT SOMETHING QUICKLY AT THE WATER LINE AGAINST THE STIMULUS WALL - NO HEAD TILT THIS TIME
